
// The code checks if an [offset] argument exists and, if so, appends an "offset" clause to an existing SQL query stored in [.sql]. It uses [exists] to verify the presence of the [offset] argument, [strings.concat] to concatenate strings, and [set-value] to update the SQL query. The [get-value] slot retrieves the current SQL query and the [offset] value.
if
   exists:x:@.arguments/*/offset
   .lambda
      set-value:x:@.sql
         strings.concat:x:@.sql
            get-value:x:@.sql
            .:" offset "
            get-value:x:@.arguments/*/offset
